# gstack Skills (vendored as submodule)

This repo vendors [gstack](https://github.com/garrytan/gstack) at `.claude/skills/gstack/`. Each skill is a folder with a `SKILL.md` that defines the procedure. Cursor cannot natively execute Claude Code slash commands, so when a user asks for one of these workflows, **read the matching `SKILL.md` and follow it as a procedure**.

After cloning, run `git submodule update --init --recursive` so the skill files exist on disk.

